public interface Modifier
extends EffDated
    Modifier Modifiers capture information relevant to the pricing of a policy that is not necessarily tied to a specific coverable or coverage.

      • checkRateFactorsAgainstProductModel

        java.util.List<? extends ProductModelSyncIssue> checkRateFactorsAgainstProductModel(Modifiable modifiable)
        Checks against the product model to find all issues involving rate factors on this modifier. None of the actions involved will be taken at this point; this will just return information about any potential problems.
        Parameters:
        modifiable - the owning modifiable
        Returns:
        list of ProductModelSyncIssues

      • clearReferenceDateInternal

        void clearReferenceDateInternal()
        Sets the ReferenceDateInternal field of this modifier to null so getReferenceDate() will compute the reference date based on the current policy data rather than returning the field's value. This is meant to be called only upon creating a new policy term (e.g., in a renewal job), when the reference dates must be recalculated.

      • denormalizeReferenceDate

        void denormalizeReferenceDate()
        Stores the current value of getReferenceDate() in the ReferenceDateInternal field of this modifier if the field is not already set, and does nothing otherwise. This is meant to be called only upon binding a policy period.

      • setRateWithinLimits

        void setRateWithinLimits(java.math.BigDecimal value)
        Sets the rate factor's Assessment property to the given value, restricting the value as necessary within the minimum/maximum limits established in the product model. If the value is below the minimum limit, the value is set with the minimum; likewise, if the value is above the maximum limit, the value is set with the the maximum.
        Parameters:
        value - - the value to be assigned

      • updateRateModifierFromRateFactors

        void updateRateModifierFromRateFactors()
        Updates the rate modifier value from the underlying rate factor array. Resets the rate modifier to 0 before beginning calculation, so any values set directly will be overwritten by what is found in the rate factors array.
